inates"><code class=3D"xref py py-obj docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">astropy.coordinates</span></code></a>.  It is provided for use=
rs if they really
want to use it, but it is recommended that you use the
<a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://docs.astropy.org/en/stable/=
coordinates/ref_api.html#module-astropy.coordinates" title=3D"astropy.coord=
inates"><code class=3D"xref py py-obj docutils literal notranslate"><span c=
lass=3D"pre">astropy.coordinates</span></code></a> coordinate systems.</p>
</div>
